Configure Mass Quick Actions on Multiple Salesforce Records from CRM Analytics Dashboards

Sometimes users want to perform the same quick action on a list of records. With CRM Analytics mass actions, users can save time by performing a quick action on up to 100 records at once from a step in CRM Analytics.

To use mass quick actions in CRM Analytics, configure mass actions for your selected Salesforce object. 

Your dashboard must contain a step for the configured object, with a query that returns the record ID. Itâ€™s best practice to include filtering that reduces the list of actionable records to 100 records or less.

In the CRM Analytics Studio, clicking a mass action link widget in a dashboard opens the action window for a user to perform quick actions on a list of records. 

Drag the link widget to the dashboard canvas.
Select the widget and enter the label that appears on the link widget.
Select Mass Action and then the step to perform the mass action on.
Select the record ID for the mass quick action to function correctly.
Select the mass quick action to perform when your link is clicked.

Save the dashboard.
title: Configure Mass Quick Actions on Salesforce Records
